article.headline: Georgia Southern 116, UC Davis 73
article.story: DURHAM, N.C. (AP) -- Donte Gennie scored 26 points and Louis Graham added 20 to lead Georgia Southern to a 116-73 victory over UC Davis on Sunday in the first round of the CBE Classic. Dwayne Foreman scored 15 points for the Eagles (1-0), who will face No. 12 Duke on Monday night in the second round of the Durham Regional. Duke beat Columbia 86-43 in the second game Sunday night. The Eagles had five players in double figures, shot 50 percent and took a 65-36 edge on the boards against the Aggies (0-1). David Carter scored 20 points to lead UC Davis, which lost Thomas Juillerat and Rommel Marentez to ankle injuries during the first half. The Aggies shot 33 percent and committed 24 turnovers that Georgia Southern converted into 27 points. Georgia Southern controlled the game almost the entire way, taking a double-digit lead midway through the first half en route to a 54-38 lead at the break. The Eagles shot 57 percent after the break to increase the lead steadily.
